Place the prawn shells and heads, chilli, tomato and stock into a saucepan. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat until the mixture is simmering and simmer for 4-5 minutes.Strain the mixture through a sieve, discarding the shells and tomato pieces. Reserve the liquid.Chop the cooked noodles and place them into a soup bowl. Pour over the fish broth.To serve, scatter over the chopped herbs.